name: autonomic nervous system neoplasm
definition: A peripheral nervous system neoplasm that is located_in the autonomic nervous system. [url:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autonomic_nervous_system]

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, Mekinist (trametinib) inhibited growth of human autonomic ganglia cancer cells harboring mutant NRAS in culture (PMID: 26343583).

references.title: Inhibition of RAF Isoforms and Active Dimers by LY3009120 Leads to Anti-tumor Activities in RAS or BRAF Mutant Cancers.
